description.p:
According to a first aspect of the present invention, there is disclosed an imaging system for imaging of materials, comprising of:
a plurality of conductive electrodes positionable in an environment to be imaged;
a signal generator connected to at least two of the electrodes;
a signal detector connected to at least two of the electrodes;
wherein the electrodes are supported on one or more conductive substrates
characterised in that it further comprises an impedance compensator arranged to counter parasitic impedance between each electrode and its substrate.
